# Weather-API-Django-

Connects to openweathermap.org/api to find and display data.


Directions for use


1.Ensure Django installed on root.
2.Navigate to projects folder on CMD and run $pipenv shell.
3.On CMD $python manage.py runserver
4.Using development server : http://127.0.0.1:8000/ connect via web browser to add/remove or alter listed cities.



Admin use: http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/
Using your code established Admin user/ password, you can add or remove authorised administrators here and view recent actions.
Can use 'edit' ~ city: to delete city from list.
